userService.register(user);

// Good: explains the non-obvious WHY
// Kafka consumer must commit offsets manually — auto-commit
// is disabled because we process in batches and only want to
// commit after the entire batch is persisted (at-least-once).
consumer.commitSync();

// Good: workaround for a known issue
// Thread.sleep here because the SQS client has a bug where
// in-flight messages are not visible to deleteMessage for
// ~50ms after receive. Remove after upgrading to aws-sdk 2.20.
Thread.sleep(100);

